originally from the feywild, silas has been with the crew ever since they were a young child - when they wandered through a rift onto the island of rumblecusp.

hot-headed and brash, silas carries a fierce intensity and is every part as wild and unpredictable as their own magic. they are the life of the party, and charge their way through life fuelled by a constant search for revelry and adrenaline in whatever form they can find.
unpredictable, and so uses the rest of her magic as means of easing and working around her chronic pain, and of creating beautiful things.

finch is a warm and genuine person, whose very presence seems to radiate a comforting aura. she is content to lead a quiet life, preferring to spend most of her days working alone in the sprawling gardens surrounding her home whilst her wives are away at sea. her druidic abilities have always been
a pact - quill’s undeath in exchange for magic and the safety of her crew, her new patron’s survival ensured by quill's own dhampiric hungers.

reserved and meticulous, quill keeps up a cold front in hopes that people will maintain their distance and leave her in peace. when an unexpected and violent storm wrecked the ship, the crew should have drowned. quill did. she was sought out by an ancient, undead sea leviathan, and they bargained
home with her wives, and co-captaining a ragtag crew of pirates alongside her wife and former rival quill, thriving on a life of hedonism and revelry.

a hot-headed and silver-tongued pirate captain, grappling with the weight of her new found dhampirism. after escaping from an abusive home and turning to piracy in hopes of creating a better life for herself and finch, harmon’s time is now split between a gentle domestic life at her lighthouse
